    <h2>Habitat</h2>
    <p>
      The Loggerhead Shrike utilizes grassland habitats that vary from shrub-steppe in the western United States to pastureland in the eastern Canadian provinces of Ontario and Quebec (Pruitt 2000).  Shrikes hunt by scanning for prey from perches in open short-grass areas, and they prefer a combination of pasture or short grassland with scattered low trees and shrubs.  But, suitable ‘habitat’ also includes rural residential development, light industrial and business parks, cemeteries and suburban parks.
    </p>
