<div class="row conservation" id="conservation" name="conservation">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h2>Conservation</h2>
    <p>Research and management needs for the Loggerhead Shrike depends upon the spatial scale of study.  Across the species’ range, research is still needed to understand the causes of the population declines, but, these may vary.  For example, the impact of pesticides and other contaminants is likely a greater concern in the areas in which such agricultural practices are common.  Collisions with roads and vehicles may be a greater threat in areas in which the species is restricted largely to road-side nest sites.  Collisions with vehicles and loss of habitat may be a problem in areas experiencing increased development.
    </p>
